grep, /bin/grep.sh
alias: 'grep'

Print lines from files or stdin
that match a Lua pattern or fixed
string.

Usage:
  grep [-F] [-i] [-n] [-v] [-r] <pattern> [file]...

  -F  fixed-string match
  -i  case-insensitive match
  -n  prefix matched lines with
      the line number
  -v  invert match: print lines that
      do not match the pattern
  -r  recurse into directories

Use '-' to read from stdin when a
shell I/O context is available.
